Book of Business Components

Use the Book of Business components to understand your business performance. They include a summary of your metrics, customer and advisor leaderboards, client segmentation charts and whitespace analysis charts.

REQUIRED EDITIONS
Available in: Developer Edition and for an extra cost in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited Editions.

The Book of Business components include:

Summary Metrics: Use these metrics to get a quick view of your business performance.
Customer Leaderboards: Quickly see which customer accounts are performing best.
Advisor Leaderboards: Quickly see which advisors are performing best.
Clients by Age Group: See the distribution of your clientsâ€™ AUM and financial accounts sorted by AgeBucket.
Whitespace Analysis: Use this chart to identify gaps in your business and uncover upsell and cross-sell opportunities.

Key Performance Indicators:

Total AUM
Wallet Share
# of Financial Accounts
Total FA Balance

The charts use Salesforce objects:

Accounts
FinancialAccount
Users

The metrics are grouped by Account Name, Owner Name, or User Name and sorted by selected metric values in descending order.

The key performance indicators for the Clients by Age Group chart include:

AUM
# of Clients

The charts use Salesforce objects:

Accounts
FinancialAccount

AgeBucket is a derived field used to group the data for these metrics. Bucketing is based on the values available in Age fields in the Account object.

Key Performance Indicators for Whitespace Analysis:

Whitespace AUM

The chart uses Salesforce objects:

Account
FinancialAccount
